LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
Moved by Galloway
Seconded by Adams
IN THE SENATE
SENATE AMENDMENT TO S.B. NO. 1141
1 AMENDMENT TO THE BILL
2 On page 1 of the printed bill, delete lines 11 through 42.
3 On page 2, delete lines 1 through 3, and insert:
4 "67-2341. PUBLIC CAMPING OR SLEEPING -- PROHIBITIONS. (1) Notwith-
5 standing any provision of law to the contrary, public camping or sleeping as
6 provided for in this section shall be unlawful in the state of Idaho. No city
7 or single countywide highway district as defined in section 40-120, Idaho
8 Code, shall authorize, permit, or enable public camping or sleeping as that
9 term is defined in this section on public property, public building grounds,
10 or public roads or rights-of-way within the jurisdiction of the city or the
11 single countywide highway district. The provisions of this section shall
12 not apply to or affect policies, rules, statutes, or leases regarding endow-
13 ment lands, department of parks and recreation lands, or department of fish
14 and game lands. The prohibitions against public camping or sleeping pro-
15 vided for in this section shall not apply to drivers of commercial vehicles
16 or commercial motor vehicles as defined in section 49-123(2)(d), Idaho Code.
17 (2) For purposes of this section, "public camping or sleeping" means
18 lodging or residing in a temporary outdoor habitation used as a dwelling,
19 lodging, or living space, which includes sitting, lying, or sleeping for a
20 prolonged amount of time, and may be evidenced by the erection of a tent or
21 other temporary shelter, including a motor vehicle as defined in section
22 39-6501, Idaho Code, or a recreational vehicle as defined in section 49-119,
23 Idaho Code, and may include but is not limited to the presence of bedding,
24 pillows, cooking appliances, heat sources, the storage of personal belong-
25 ings or food, or digging or earth breaking.
26 (3) Nothing in this section shall prohibit or prevent overnight camp-
27 ing for recreational or educational purposes on property designated for such
28 purpose, authorized specific temporary events or activities, or authorized
29 overnight parking at Idaho rest areas or private businesses in compliance
30 with applicable established rules. Nothing in this section shall prohibit
31 or restrict a city or single countywide highway district from maintaining
32 and enforcing ordinances, rules, or laws that prohibit loitering, overnight
33 camping, or other similar activities.
34 (4) The attorney general shall have the power to bring a civil action
35 in any court of competent jurisdiction against any city or single county-
36 wide highway district to enjoin the city or countywide highway district from
37 knowingly violating the provisions of this section. The attorney general
38 may recover reasonable expenses incurred in any civil action brought under
39 this section, including court costs, reasonable attorney's fees, investiga-
40 tive costs, witness fees, and deposition costs. Any city or single county-

2
1 wide highway district that violates the provisions of this section may be as-
2 sessed a civil penalty of not more than ten thousand dollars ($10,000) for
3 each violation. Cities or single countywide highway districts against whom
4 civil penalties are assessed are liable for reasonable attorney's fees.
5 (5) The provisions of this section shall apply only to property within
6 city limits for cities with a population of greater than or equal to one hun-
7 dred thousand (100,000).".
8 CORRECTION TO TITLE
9 On page 1, in line 4, delete "UNAUTHORIZED" and insert: "PROHIBITIONS
10 ON"; and in line 5, delete "AND TO PROVIDE FOR A CAUSE OF ACTION;" and insert:
11 "TO PROVIDE FOR A CAUSE OF ACTION, AND TO PROVIDE FOR CIVIL PENALTIES;".

